comments.body:
@edsantiago the goal is to bubble the Warnings up to the user, when the user can take action.  If the user can not take action, then I believe that these should be dropped down to info.

The example that spawned this is building an OCI image with a Containerfile field that is not supported.  Currently we warn and then build the image without the field.  It would be better to warn the users so that they could fix their Containerfile without the option or build with --format docker.

Hopefully we will quickly flush out the log messages that should not be presented to the user.
